<%# Account switcher stub (requirement.md §4.11/§9 — full cross-tenant relay-token SSO switching
    is Phase 17). Rendered only on the tenant side — shared/_console_shell guards this on
    Current.account, which is nil on the Platform Console (Super Admin has no AccountMembership
    at all, §4.1). Reads real AccountMembership data now rather than hardcoding "no other
    accounts": the join table already supports a User belonging to several Accounts (the agency
    use case, §4.11) even though nothing lets a user actually acquire a second membership yet
    (no invite-to-another-account flow exists before Phase 17 either) — today that means every
    real user hits the "no other accounts" branch honestly, not as a hardcoded stand-in for it. %>
<div class="px-3 py-2">
  <div class="dropdown">
    <button class="btn btn-sm btn-outline-secondary dropdown-toggle w-100 text-start d-flex align-items-center"
            type="button" data-bs-toggle="dropdown" aria-expanded="false">
      <i class="bx bx-buildings me-2 flex-shrink-0"></i>
      <span class="text-truncate"><%= Current.account.name %></span>
    </button>
    <ul class="dropdown-menu w-100">
      <% other_accounts = current_user.accounts.where.not(id: Current.account.id) %>
      <% if other_accounts.any? %>
        <% other_accounts.each do |account| %>
          <li><span class="dropdown-item-text small text-muted"><%= account.name %></span></li>
        <% end %>
      <% else %>
        <li><span class="dropdown-item-text small text-muted">No other accounts</span></li>
      <% end %>
    </ul>
  </div>
</div>
